# Senticient Feedback System Standards

## System Overview
- Automated post-class surveys via SMS (ClickSend).
- Analytics to identify "at-risk" students.
- Supabase heartbeat to prevent project pausing.
- Branding: Senticient (Navy/Sky Blue theme).

## SMS Delivery (ClickSend)
- **SDK**: Use the official `clicksend` Node.js SDK for all messaging.
- **Campaigns**: Use ClickSend SMS Campaigns for URL shortening and unique link tracking.
- **Direct Messaging**: Admins can send ad-hoc SMS to students via the dashboard.
- **Admin Copies**: Courses can be configured to include admins in all survey SMS deliveries.
- **Tracking**: Reconcile ClickSend tracking data back to students via phone numbers.
- **Opt-out**: Mandatory "Reply STOP to opt out" in all SMS bodies.
- **Reference**: Follow the integration plan in `docs/CLICKSEND_CAMPAIGNS.md`.

## Scheduling & Crons (Vercel)
- **Send Survey**: `/api/cron/send-surveys` (Tue/Thu at 9:00 PM America/Chicago).
- **Tracking Sync**: `/api/cron/pull-click-tracking` (Hourly).
- **Sentiment & Trends**: `/api/cron/analyze` (Daily at 2:30 AM).
- **Heartbeat**: `/api/cron/heartbeat` (Sun/Wed at 3:00 AM).
- **Idempotency**: Always verify `send_log` or session status before sending to prevent duplicates.
- **Security**: All cron routes must verify `CRON_SECRET` in headers and use `createAdminClient`.
- **Reference**: See `vercel.json` for schedules.

## Analytics & "At-Risk" Logic
- **At-Risk Flags**:
  - Rolling 3-session average rating/confidence drops by >= 1.0 vs baseline.
  - Negative sentiment in 2 consecutive sessions.
- **Sentiment Analysis**: Use heuristic scoring (implemented in `/api/cron/analyze`) initially.
- **Reference**: See `docs/PRD.md` for logic details.

## Database & Security
- **RLS**: 
  - Students: INSERT only their own response.
  - Admin: Full access to courses they administer via `is_course_admin(course_id)`.
- **Tables**: Follow schema in `supabase/migrations/0001_init.sql`.

## Implementation Guidance
- When building features, refer to `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`.
- Use the multi-agent workflow defined in `docs/multi-agent-workflow.md`.
